   "body" : "TLDR: Replace two tools that we build and maintain in depends, as part of our macOS deployment, with one that we don't.\r\n\r\nCarl mentioned that [`xorriso`](https://www.gnu.org/software/xorriso/) ([Debian package](https://packages.debian.org/search?keywords=xorriso)) could replace our usage of `libdmg-hfsplus` and `genisoimage`. Looks like that's possible. Have tested gitian builds, and reproducibility looks good. Looking for Concept ACKs.\r\n\r\nAlso related to #18128, as this eliminates some dependencies. Will post thoughts on using a `.zip` for distribution there.\r\n\r\n#### TODO:\r\n- [ ] `xorrisofs` vs calling `xorriso -as mkisofs`\r\n- [ ] Compression. Passing `zisofs level=9` etc.",
